text: Centre Pompidou Renzo Piano and Richard Rogers Paris FranceCentre Pompidou houses a multicultural complex bringing together in one place different forms of art and literature the Public Information Library the Mus e National d Art Moderne and IRCAM a centre for music and acoustic research It is named Georges Pompidou the President of France who commissioned the building The Rogers and Piano design was chosen among competition entries and world renowned architects such as Oscar Niemeyer Jean Prouv and Philip Johnson made up the jury It was the first major example of an inside out building in architectural history with its structural system mechanical systems and circulation exposed on the exterior of the building following the style of high tech architecture Most of the functional structural elements are colour coded green pipes are plumbing blue ducts are for climate control electrical wires are encased in yellow and circulation elements and devices for safety are red Have you already visited it pillarsofarchitecture pillarsofarchitecture unknown renzopiano rogers centrepompidou pompidoucentre architecturelovers architecturestudentbelike architecture view architecture best paris beauborg hightech competitionarchitects insideout structure structuralelements polimi multicultural complex library museum music

text: DIGITAL LIBRARY For AAP s th anniversary issue we invited two international curators Yung Ma and Clara Kim to discuss the global curatorial future from the history of art institutions to possible new models of acquiring art in an increasingly engaging art world Toward the end of their conversation Ma predicted Since the notion of curating has become quite democratised and knowledge of art will be more a part of mass culture the public will have strong opinions about how and what kind of art is presented Link in bio Yung Ma has just been appointed as the artistic director of the Seoul Mediacity Biennale Pictured Still from Nanette a live recording of a stand up comedy set by Tasmanian comic and art critic Hannah Gadsby Photo by Ben King Courtesy Netflix YungMa ClaraKim curator CentrePompidou TateModern artconversation SeoulMediacityBiennale democratization highart popculture

text: throwback Thicket struikgewas by Maya Dunietz at Centre Pompidou Paris On the first floor the viewer immerses in a cloud made of thousands of headphones A look from above unveils the cloud origin on an upper level balcony The thicket floods the space with humming white particles The sounds coming out of the headphones as well as the sounds emerging from the balcony of the gallery are an invitation to investigate the space exposing a unique acoustic phenomena that comes to life as the audience moves around the room while this Thicket is singing its song other sounds are heard in the space sounds that we can hear but not yet see low mumbles and groans and birds echoing from the second floor mayadunietz mayadunietzthicket headphones contemporaryart modernart art paris centrepompidou thicket museum france

text: In October of at the Museum of Modern Art in Paris I noticed the large windows between the paintings interested me more than the art exhibited I made a drawing of the window and later in my studio I made what I considered my first object Window Museum of Modern Art Paris From then on painting as I had known it was finished for me The new works were to be paintings objects unsigned anonymous Everywhere I looked everything I saw became something to be made and it had to be made exactly as it was with nothing added It was a new freedom there was no longer the need to compose The subject was there already made and I could take from everything it all belonged to me a glass roof of a factory with its broken and patched panes lines of a roadmap the shape of a scarf on a woman s head a fragment of Le Corbusier s Swiss Pavilion a corner of a Braque painting paper fragments in the street It was all the same anything goes Ellsworth Kelly in Coplans pp years ago age Ellsworth KellyWindow Museum of Modern Art Paris oil on wood and canvas two joined panelsCentre national d art et de culture Georges Pompidou Gift of the artist centrepompidou museedartmodernedeparis Still image from checkerboardfilms ELLSWORTH KELLY FRAGMENTS available to download or on DVD ellsworthkelly parismuseumofmodenart centrepompidou jackshear

text: PROYECTO DE MUSEO SOBRE CASTLLO EN PONFERRADAComienzan las obras Santalla StrartS y QuinSan han creado la Asociaci n de Museos Virtuales cuyo fin es que todos los pueblos independientemente de su poblaci n puedan disponer de un museo de arte El lema es NING N PUEBLO SIN MUSEO Una vez inaugurados podr n programarse exposiciones temporales o permanentes Los tres primeros museos ya se han inaugurado en Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata y Madrid El pr ximo ser en Ponferrada y despu s en Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada PROJECT OF MUSEUM ON CASTLE IN PONFERRADAThe works begin Santalla StrartS and QuinSan have created the Association of Virtual Museums whose goal is that all peoples regardless of their population can have an art museum The motto is NO PEOPLE WITHOUT MUSEUM Once opened temporary or permanent exhibitions may be scheduled The first three museums have already opened in Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata and Madrid The next one will be in Ponferrada and then in Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada reinasofiamuseum museodelprado caixaforum museothyssen hermitagemuseum whitneymuseum centrepompidou nationalgallery moma museedorsay louvre met salvadordalimuseum britishmuseum tatemodern guggenheim nycart brooklynmuseum lacmamuseum gemaldegalerie artinstitutechicago ufizzi louvreabudhabi galleriaborghese gettymuseum yaleartgallery sfmoma nationalgalleryofart altepinakothek rijksmuseum

text: Fans can look forward to a potential collaboration between the Centre Pompidou and BTS On August Herald Biz reported that the Centre Pompidou had offered to make their art museum available for BTS s use The Centre Pompidou is a building complex in Paris France with a deep architectural and artistic significance Around five million people visit the complex every year and like France s other esteemed art museums including the Louvre Museum and Mus e d Orsay it is seldom made available to a specific group for filming purposes Based on Herald Biz s report the Centre Pompidou offered to open a part of its complex to BTS in June which is around the time they held their Love Yourself Speak Yourself concert at the Stade de France At the time RM had posted a photo of himself in front of the complex though it unknown whether his visit to the Centre had any relation to the offer they had received Are you excited for this collaboration Admin jae kpop kpopsl bts btsarmy btsarmysl slkpop kpopinsrilanka jhope jungkook kookie jimin rapmonster namjoon jin v taehyung korea southkorea france centrepompidou art slkpop bangtanboys lights boyinluv srilanka colombo

text: INFO Os f s podem esperar uma colabora o potencial entre o Centre Pompidou e o BTS Em de agosto o Herald Biz informou que o Centre Pompidou se ofereceu para disponibilizar seu museu de arte para uso do BTS O Centre Pompidou um complexo de edif cios em Paris na Fran a com um profundo significado arquitet nico e art stico Cerca de cinco milh es de pessoas visitam o complexo todos os anos e como outros museus de arte da Fran a como o Museu do Louvre e o Mus e d Orsay raramente s o disponibilizados para um grupo espec fico para fins de filmagem Com base no relat rio do Herald Biz o Centre Pompidou ofereceu se para abrir uma parte do seu complexo para o BTS em junho que na poca em que eles realizaram seu show Love Yourself Speak Yourself no Stade de France Na poca RM havia postado uma foto sua em frente ao complexo embora n o se saiba se sua visita ao Centro tinha alguma rela o com a oferta que haviam recebido Embora a oferta tenha sido feita antes de seu show em Paris o Centre Pompidou tamb m estaria disposto a abrir v rias reas incluindo seu telhado no futuro para a BTS filmar fotos e v deos para finalidades como filmagens de videoclipes e upload de m dia social A oferta ainda n o foi revelada publicamente porque o acordo ainda est sendo discutido entre o Centre Pompidou e a Big Hit Entertainment Fonte SoompiTR TP K POP NEWS MMN o retirar os devidos cr ditos n kpop bts centrepompidou

text: POSCAST LA RENCONTRE DE GERMAINE KRULLFigure majeure de la photographie moderne GermaineKrull a travers la guerre et la r volution en s engageant corps et me C est sa vie de militante qui est mise en lumi re dans ce podcast travers des extraits de son autobiographie La vie m ne la danse et des entretiens avec Fran oise Denoyelle historienne de la photographie et Florian Ebner conservateur et Directeur du Cabinet de la Photographie du Centre Pompidou NO BORDERS SANS FRONTI RESDiffus s tout au long de l t chaque pisode donne la parole une photographe ayant expos aux rencontresarles et dont les oeuvres font partie de la collection du centrepompidou A couter sur rencontres arles com fr podcasts centrepompidou fr sur l application ARLES POSCAST MEETING WITH GERMAINE KRULLA major figure in modern photography GermaineKrull went through war and revolution by committing herself body and soul This podcast highlights her life as an activist through excerpts from her autobiography Life Leads the Dance and interviews with photography historian Fran oise Denoyelle and Florian Ebner curator and head of the Pompidou Centre s Photography Department NO BORDERS SANS FRONTI RESBroadcast all summer each episode features a photographer who has exhibited at the rencontresarles and whose works are in the centrepompidou Listen to this podcast at rencontres arles com en podcasts centrepompidou fr and on the ARLES app rencontres arles photographie photography exposition exhibition podcast centrepompidou

text: INAUGURACI N EXPOSICI N EN EL MUSEO DE SAN JUAN DE LA MATAEl de julio de se ha inaugurado una nueva exposici n con el t tulo EL FUEGO EN EL PRADOHomenaje al Museo del Prado en su Bicentenario Complementa y ampl a la exposici n anterior sobre el mismo tema pero con obras pertenecientes al Museo del Prado Vel zquez Rubens Goya El Bosco Cossiers Y como plato fuerte Un cuadro viviente Santalla StrartS y QuinSan han creado la Asociaci n de Museos Virtuales cuyo fin es que todos los pueblos independientemente de su poblaci n puedan disponer de un museo de arte El lema es NING N PUEBLO SIN MUSEO INAUGURATION EXHIBITION AT THE SAN JUAN DE LA MATA MUSEUMOn July a new exhibition with the title was inaugurated THE FIRE IN THE PRADOTribute to the Prado Museum in its BicentennialIt complements and extends the previous exhibition on the same subject but with works belonging to the Museo del Prado Vel zquez Rubens Goya El Bosco Cossiers And as a main course A living painting Santalla StrartS and QuinSan have created the Association of Virtual Museums whose goal is that all peoples regardless of their population can have an art museum The motto is NO PEOPLE WITHOUT MUSEUM museodelprado reinasofiamuseum caixaforum museothyssen hermitagemuseum whitneymuseum centrepompidou nationalgallery moma modernart museedorsay louvre met britishmuseum tatemodern guggenheim nycart brooklynmuseum lacmamuseum gemaldegalerie artinstitutechicago ufizzi louvreabudhabi yaleartgallery galleriaborghese gettymuseum sfmoma nationalgalleryofart altepinakothek rijksmuseum

text: Confirm stunning multiple reflections fracture with this serie of hanging spheres called StardustParticle images to Tate presented by the artist in honour of Sir Nicholas Serota T ColdWindSphere img to gift of the clarenceWesburyFoundation centrepompidou Paris National Museum of Modern Art IndustrialCreationCentre X Kaleidoscopes tateModern tatecollective OLAFURELIASSON studioolafureliasson with this unmissable inRealLife exhibitionWhere he creates engaging artworks inspired by his interests in perception colour movement and the interaction of people and their environments Social and environmental issues lie at the heart of his work Some artworks introduce natural phenomena such as rainbows to the gallery space Others use reflections and shadows to play with the way we perceive and interact with the world Many works result from the artist s research into complex geometry motion patterns and his interest in colour theory Within the exhibition will be an area which explores Eliasson s deep engagement with society and the environment Discover what an artist s perspective can bring to issues of climate change energy migration as well as architecture And once every other week you ll be able to communicate with people from Eliasson s strong team in his Berlin studio via a live link love art artlover beautiful best way of spending time with my girls BeInspired BeSpontaneous BeRelaxed BeImmersed BeTogether BeConnected BePioneering BeCaptivated ContemporaryArt WorldPhotographyDay

text: Posted withrepost galerieperrotin There are only a few days left to visit Bernard Frize s solo show at Centre Pompidou Mus e National d Art Moderne in Paris Throughout his four decades long career Bernard Frize has used his practice to question pictorial practices and the role of the painter At a time marked by rapid technological advancement and extensive focus on moving images Bernard Frize is committed to examining the challenges of painting Dive into his exhibition Bernard Frize Without remorse through August Bernard Frize Without remorse Centre Pompidou Paris Through August bernardfrize centrepompidou BernardFrize ExpoBernardFrize CentrePompidou Perrotin Bernard Frize Emir Acrylic nacre ink and resin on canvas x cm x inch Exhibition views of Bernard Frize Without remorse at Centre Pompidou Courtesy Perrotin the artist artandartist artandartist

text: If in Paris MUST SEE centrepompidou superb exhibition coming soon BACON EN TOUTES LETTRES Upcoming exhibition September January The Center Pompidou exhibition focuses on works by Bacon during the last two decades of his work It comprises sixty paintings including triptychs as well as a series of portraits and self portraits from the most important private and public collections From to date of the painter s death the painting is stylistically marked by its simplification by its intensification His colors acquire a new depth he uses a new chromatic register yellow pink saturated orange I try to give myself excitement and also to make a work as resistant as possible because I like powerful and resistant things I do not like art that is very fragile Francis BaconCredits Picture Francis Bacon Selfportrait Philippe Migeat centre Pompidou MNAM CCI Dist RMN GP The estate of Francis Bacon All rights reserved Adagp Paris and DACS Londres Picture Cecil Beaton Francis Bacon in His Studio image Christie s Picture Francis Bacon Triptych The estate of Francis Bacon All rights reserved DACS Artimage Photos Hugo Maertens Picture Francis Bacon Portrait of George Dyer in a Mirror The estate of Francis Bacon All rights reserved DACS Artimage Photos Hugo Maertens Picture Francis Bacon Three Portraits Posthumous of George Dyer Self Portrait Portrait of Lucian Freud The estate of Francis Bacon All rights reserved DACS Artimage Photos Prudence Cumins Associates Ltd francisbacon francisbaconart francisbaconartist francisbaconexhibition centrepompidou parisexhibition paris parisart artexhibition art artcollection painter paintings surrealisme surrealismart artsureealiste artfiguratif artcubiste

text: A letter from Shanghai This week marked the th month anniversary of the opening of CamronShanghai time flies The team is growing the office is taking shape and our neighbours theartling stellar works and muutodesign are all opening showrooms on the ground floor Even in the heat this city doesn t seem to slow down From left to right here we share some highlights of our busy summer Experts in hospitality we were fascinated this week when we learned about Yellow River Hotel Group and their new community hotel concept in ZhengWei which is changing the way we look at hotel design and the overall hospitality experience Yellow River Hotel Group Reinventing spaces for work and leisure last month paper shanghai opened a new creative workspace and design library specifically to empower young designers architects photographers and creative professionals with all the tools they need to create their best work Members have access to architectural material samples textiles drafting tools D printing as well as a full service photography studio and consulting services Paper Shanghai China s art migration for a long time Beijing has been the centre of China s burgeoning art community However with the rise of rents artists are relocating here and even international art museums are placing their bets on Shanghai The centrepompidou will open an outpost in Shanghai s West Bund District this November while lacma is partnering with yuzmuseum with a collaborative debut this autumn westbundartfair now in its th year has solidified its position on the global arts calendar for international galleries and Asian collectors West Bund Group shanghai theartling stellarworks muutodesign yellowriverhotelgroup zhengwei papershanghai centrepompidou westbunddistrict lacma yuzmuseum designshanghai artshanghai asiancollectors westbundartfair

text: MUSEO LAPUEBLA DE LABARCA FELICES FIESTAS Santalla StrartS y QuinSan han creado la Asociaci n de Museos Virtuales cuyo fin es que todos los pueblos independientemente de su poblaci n puedan disponer de un museo de arte El lema es NING N PUEBLO SIN MUSEO Una vez inaugurados podr n programarse exposiciones temporales o permanentes Los tres primeros museos ya se han inaugurado en Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata y Madrid El pr ximo ser en Ponferrada y despu s en Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada LAPUEBLA DE LABARCA MUSEUMHAPPY HOLIDAYS Santalla StrartS and QuinSan have created the Association of Virtual Museums whose goal is that all peoples regardless of their population can have an art museum The motto is NO PEOPLE WITHOUT MUSEUM Once opened temporary or permanent exhibitions may be scheduled The first three museums have already opened in Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata and Madrid The next one will be in Ponferrada and then in Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada reinasofiamuseum museodelprado caixaforum museothyssen hermitagemuseum whitneymuseum centrepompidou nationalgallery moma modernart museedorsay louvre met britishmuseum tatemodern guggenheim nycart brooklynmuseum lacmamuseum gemaldegalerie artinstitutechicago ufizzi louvreabudhabi yaleartgallery galleriaborghese gettymuseum sfmoma nationalgalleryofart altepinakothek rijksmuseum

text: PROYECTO DE MUSEO SOBRE CASTILLO EN PONFERRADAContin an las obras Santalla StrartS y QuinSan han creado la Asociaci n de Museos Virtuales cuyo fin es que todos los pueblos independientemente de su poblaci n puedan disponer de un museo de arte El lema es NING N PUEBLO SIN MUSEO Una vez inaugurados podr n programarse exposiciones temporales o permanentes Los tres primeros museos ya se han inaugurado en Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata y Madrid El pr ximo ser en Ponferrada y despu s en Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada PROJECT OF MUSEUM ON CASTLE IN PONFERRADAThe works continue Santalla StrartS and QuinSan have created the Association of Virtual Museums whose goal is that all peoples regardless of their population can have an art museum The motto is NO PEOPLE WITHOUT MUSEUM Once opened temporary or permanent exhibitions may be scheduled The first three museums have already opened in Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata and Madrid The next one will be in Ponferrada and then in Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada reinasofiamuseum museodelprado caixaforum museothyssen hermitagemuseum whitneymuseum centrepompidou nationalgallery moma museedorsay louvre met salvadordalimuseum britishmuseum tatemodern guggenheim nycart brooklynmuseum lacmamuseum gemaldegalerie artinstitutechicago ufizzi louvreabudhabi galleriaborghese gettymuseum yaleartgallery sfmoma nationalgalleryofart altepinakothek rijksmuseum

text: Ren Magritte The False Mirror oil on canvas x cm Museum of Modern Art New York Ren Magritte was a Belgian painter draughtsman printmaker sculptor photographer and film maker He was one of the major figures of Surrealism and perhaps the greatest Belgian artist of the th century His oeuvre is characterised by scenes in which objects and people are combined together in an unusual way and placed in an unusual setting Unlike other Surrealists Magritte was inspired by ordinary objects to wich he gave a twist rather than the subconscious and dream images Magritte loved confronting the viewer with an image that looks deceptively real and provokes questions An explanation of the work is often unclear however and left up to the viewer to decide For the surrealists the human eye was an important motif in their art Max Ernst Salvador Dali and Man Ray all made use of it Magritte presents us with a large unblinking eye with no eyelashes in The False Mirror A large black pupil is located in the centre By replacing the eyes iris with a blue and cloudy sky Magritte raises many questions about human nature and how we perceive the world and those around us He challenges us to question what we literally and figuratively see and what we think we know The title might suggests we are looking through a window that is in the shape of an eye The Surrealist photographer Man Ray owned the work from to He described The False Mirror as a painting that sees as much as it itself is seen How would you explain or interpret this famous work Check out my other accounts art questions and debates my favorite work of art ren magritte renemagritte magritte thefalsemirror lefauxmiroir surrealism belgianpainter moma museumofmodernart centrepompidou instaart artcurator artblog onlineart artinfo artgallery artmuseum arthistorian

text: DORA MAAR Portrait of Ubu It s a sweet souvenir of my time at la Sorbonne during my Art History Studies Alfred Jarry s play Ubu Roi was appreciated for the absurdity of his protagonist Ubu by the Surrealists Dora Maar always preserved her work s mystery by not clarifying if it was indeed an armadillo foetus Half way between monstrous and adorable the lighting emphasises the antagonism of the feelings regarding this artwork It is what it makes it fascinating if you ask me centrepompidou Portrait d Ubu En voil un doux souvenir de mes tudes en Histoire de l Art La Sorbonne Les surr alistes ont particuli rement appr ci la pi ce de d Alfred Jarry Ubu Roi pour l absurdity de son protagoniste Ubu Dora Maar a toujours gard le myst re de cette uvre en ne pr cisant jamais s il agissait effectivement d un foetus de tatou mi chemin entre l adorable et la monstruosit l clairage accentue l antagonisme des sentiments vis vis de cette uvre C est ce qui la rend fascinante mon avis

text: In Joan Mir left his native country of Spain for France where along with fellow Spaniard Salvador Dal he became one of the pioneers of Surrealism Inspired by the movement s engagement with psychology and poetic play with form Mir developed a dreamlike style based on whimsical allusions to reality and lyrical fancifully colored compositions This work is part of the Constellations series which was produced over months from January to September Characteristic of the works begun at the end of his stay in France and those painted in Spain the entire sheet of paper is covered with hourglass shapes and a multitude of forms suggesting stars eyes circles triangles and crescents that are linked by thin black lines to evoke a fantastical wrought iron screen or perhaps a magical constellation in the cosmos Each picture took about a month to complete joanmiro mir surrealism centrepompidou pompidou artoftheday art prehistoireuneenigmemoderne pr histoire

text: Prehistorian cave art was first discovered only about years ago Since then it influenced many modern artists OUBEY loved it because it is of a lively kind of immediacy and connectedness with nature by the use of primitive devices and colors only The ancient artists captured what was most impressive and important to them I completely share OUBEYs love for prehistoric art and so I took the chance to see the current exhibition at Centre Pompidou in Paris titled Prehistory A Modern Enigma It s running by th September The pic shows a try from st century to meet and honor the great and sovereign art of our ancient ancestors It s a detail of an impressive piece by Miquel Barcelo titled Le Grand Verre de Terre Vidre de meravelles art artist prehistory cave caveart cavepaintings ancestors influence paris modernart centrepompidou exhibition recommended oubey mindkiss immediacy nature lively expression enigma stcentury stoneage

text: I was surprised when I was standing in front of the Centre Pompidou for the first time It felt a little bit like lego stones put into an old city on a very frequented road I didn t get it why I liked it so much on the pictures at first There was now way you could see whole length of the facade at once because it was so close You only see big colored tubes in front of you but you can see them everywhere and oh man they are massive And those views were the real charm of that building for me It only took me two days to recognize it It really is one of the landmarks of Paris paris centrepompidou architecture france museum art modernart summer

text: Ida Tursic Wilfried Mille are nominated for the Prix Marcel Duchamp The exhibition will take place at Centre Pompidou in Paris from October th to January The Prix Marcel Duchamp reflects above all the collector s view the view of the informed and enthusiastic lay art lover of the French scene today But beyond the very wide ranging roster of artists shortlisted since a glimpse of the vast artistic panorama of our times the prize is also the vehicle of a humanist message reflecting the French spirit of open mindedness and even handedness that I value enormously and which seems to me ever more important to defend in the divided world we live in Founded by the aDiaF in open to French and French based artists and organised from the first in partnership with the Centre Pompidou the Prix Marcel Duchamp has made its mark as one of the most effective vehicles for raising awareness of contemporary art in France gaining a prestige that makes it one of the most important of national prizes on the international scene Deliberately intended to recognise the most innovative artists of their generation the Prix Marcel Duchamp seeks to promote the whole spectrum of contemporary art while setting different forms and practices into dialogue The prize has to date been awarded to artists from among some shortlisted candidates Gilles Fuchs IdaTursic WilfriedMille idatursicetwilfriedmille PrixMarcelDuchamp CentrePompidou Adiaf adiaf o centrepompidou AlmineRech AlmineRechGallery

text: I was pleasantly surprised today that JeanHubertMartin sent me the recent issue of the French art magazine Mettray with his text about my artwork Les Absents ont Toujours Tort that I made in and which is included in the collection of the centrepompidou in Paris It is a great honor for me that Jean Hubert Martin compares my work with MarcelDuchamp s text D ailleurs c est toujours les autres qui meurent This epitaph written by Marcel Duchamp for himself and inscribed on the Duchamp family tombstone in Rouen means Anyway it s always the others who die This September issue of Mettray published by DidierMorin has the theme Inscriptions drawing and writing and in addition to the images has been executed entirely in the handwriting of the collaborators A larger version in red marble of my work with the same title has been installed on the Damplein in Middelburg the Netherlands since as part of the PodioDelMondoPerLArte initiated by marinusboezem lesabsentsonttoujourstort conceptart billytown bookshelves artistsbooks artistsdocumentation thearchivespetervanbeverenlibrary vanbeverenexpertise

text: tbt art stico Fiquei observando alguns minutos essa obra no Pompideu pra entender do que se tratava Olhei de perto de longe e algo me intrigava At entender o que fato se tratava o pintor chama se Yves Klein amante do canibalismo Ele pintou os corpos de modelos de azul e os fez rolarem na tela como se estivessem cometendo canibalismo Muito louco n o O mais fascinante desses quadros entender o racional por tr s das obras I would like now with your permission and attention to divulge to you possibly the most important and certainly the most secret phase of my art I don t know whether you will believe it or not it s cannibalism After all wouldn t it be better to be eaten than to be bombed I can hardly document this idea that has been tormenting me for some years so I will leave it up to you to make your own conclusions on what I think will be the future of art Yves Klein arts artist modern centrepompidou pompidou paris parisfrance artes artemoderna france culture

text: We re back at work and excited for this fall s exciting new experiences planned for our customers We will discover blockbuster exhibitions Leonardo at the Louvre Francis Bacon at Centre Pompidou Toulouse Lautrec and El Greco at Grand Palais and Charlotte Perriand at Fondation Louis Vuitton to name just a few more confidential ones can t wait to see Modern Maharaja at MAD Paris and L Asie Maintenant at Guimet and contemporary art galleries in the run up to FIAC opening on October th Our patrons days aren t filled just with art our discoveries include cooking classes wine tastings interior design or antiques shopping trips and much more To top it all off we recommend the best restaurants and cocktail bars the city has to offer with many new openings scheduled for the autumn If you are planning a Paris get away for the fall don t hesitate to get in touch Whether it s a family vacation a girls weekend or even a wedding party to keep entertained in the run up to the big day we will tailor a stay to your needs and interests taking care of everything so you don t need to venividiparis leonardodavinci francisbacon toulouselautrec elgreco charlotteperriand louvre centrepompidou grandpalais fondationlv madparis museeguimet fiac parismuseums parisigers parisfrance travelinsider curatedtravel tailormadetravel parisisalwaysagoodidea venividiparis parisianadventureswithvvp

text: Takis Signals are the first important works created by the artist in Paris in after a figurative beginning Made of thin steel rods bearing metal recycled elements they reveal an industrial universe that the artist discovers in Calais station fascinated by a forest of signals Monster eyes lit and extinguished rails tunnels an iron jungle Multicoloured signs railings passages From the very beginning of his Signals Takis paid extreme attention to technological modernity seeking to transform the relationships between art and science The sculptures will then be constantly modified in order to launch fireworks rockets Signal Fireworks to wear coloured light bulbs Signal Light Gradually they increased in height reaching six metres in Jean Paul Ameline extract from the catalogue Collection art contemporain La collection du Centre Pompidou Mus e national d art moderne under the direction of Sophie Duplaix Paris Centre Pompidou Triple signal sold euros takis signals sculptor steel greeksculpture contemporarysculpture centrepompidou auction

text: TYP Art Vote The Terror Of War Art is not only for joy and pleasure it also helps raise public awareness and engage people During the peaceful time the terror of war may be forgotten But the artworks from those war time remain a sharp reminder This week TYP ART CRUISE presents a selection of artworks witnessing the wars in different ways At the end of the week come to my FB page and vote for the most powerful one Today s artwork is an installation created by Arman Fernandez in It is a very powerful work which has anchored in my memory since I discovered it at Centre Pompidou in Paris The artist gathered many gas masks in a plexiglass box and named it Home Sweet Home These gas masks remind us of the millions of people killed in the First World War Toxic chemicals were used by both Germany and the Allies as they could reach deep into the front trenches A hundred years late the chemical attacks still keep happening despite international condemnation typartlove typartlearning typartsharing typartvote typartcruise art artwork installation modernart arthistory artdiscovery artist nouveaurealisme centrepompidou armanfernandez homesweethome gasmask glassbox worldwarone wwi firstworldwar war wars theterrorofwar gasattack chemicalattack memory americanartist toxic

text: STEFAN BR GGEMANN HEADLINES AND LAST LINES IN THE MOVIES GUERNICA A MONUMENTAL WORK IN THE FORUM SEPTEMBER MUSEUM FORUMThe Centre Pompidou is proud to exhibit an original monumental painting by German Mexicanartist Stefan Br ggemann Headlines and Last Lines in the Movies Guernica coinciding with the Extra literary festival and resonating with the Francis Bacon Books and Painting exhibition A mirror work of art on both sides comprising multicoloured writing to saturation point this major work by Stefan Br ggemann will be freely accessible for a month through to September Stefan Br ggemann is a visual artist born in in Mexico of German and Mexican nationality and divides his time between Mexico City and London His work features written words phrases or sentences on walls or his canvases It not only has a hyper visual focus it is also hyper textual in that text is a constant source for him even a raw material he uses in every way possible The texts in his works are sometimes conceptual usually newspaper extracts or film titles and may be crossed out or overlaid conferring them with great plasticity in their form it is this combination of the materiality of the text and the plasticity of his artistic language This exhibition benefits from the generosity of Mr Eugenio Lopez and the support of the Hauser Wirth Gallery centrepompidou centrepompidouparis stefanbruggemann stefanbr ggemann hauserwirth hauser wirth conceptualpop minimalism installationart popart conceptualart gesture political paris culture art contemporaryart ADMISSION AND PRICESCentre Pompidou Paris cedex

text: ARTE INFINITO Conocido por mi madre como el Scooby Doo el Centre Pompidou alberga el IRCAM centro de investigaci n musical la Biblioth que Publique d Information y el Mus e National d Art Moderne uno de los m s completos de arte moderno junto con el MoMA de Nueva York y el Tate Modern de Londres En la d cada del unos j venes Renzo Piano y Richard Rogers ganaron el concurso para erguir uno de los primeros ejemplos de arquitectura high tech con la idea de destripar el edificio Los huesos y las entra as quedar an expuestas Conductos de ventilaci n instalaciones escaleras e incluso la estructura met lica por fuera y con colores estridentes El resultado un espacio interior despojado ideal para ambientes polivalentes donde alojar cualquier tipo de actividad art stica Cualquiera pensar a que rompe con la imagen rom ntica de Par s pero realmente se integra perfectamente con el espacio circundante La explanada contigua baja hasta introducirse literalmente por debajo del edificio y alrededor del Pompidou se respira el arte contempor neo que parece no poder contenerse dentro de l y explota por todo el barrio La estructura modular da la idea de una infinita y posible repetici n Quiz s haya que repartir el arte hasta el infinito para que se infiltre en cada rinc n de Par s ya que como le mos en la plaza contigua life without art is stupid centrepompidou centregeorgespompidou modernart artemoderno arquitectura architecture hightech renzopiano richardrogers paris france francia

text: I discovered David Hockney s work on an exhibition at Centre Pompidou years ago and he s become one of my favourite artists Portrait of an Artist Pool with Two Figures is worth million which makes it the most expensive work of art by a living artist sold at auction On a trip to LA he was struck to the blue swimming pools all over a swimming pool in England would have been a luxury whereas here they are not Without realising it he had discovered his greatest subject LA s pools would become the setting for many of his major works of the s and s The city s private backyard swimming pools provided him with a space in which he was free to explore the male figure The Tate Britain s retrospective which toured to the Centre Pompidou in Paris and the Met in New York attracted almost half a million people becoming Tate s most visited exhibition ever davidhockney tatebritain centrepompidou art pool la

text: PROYECTO DE MUSEO SOBRE CASTILLO EN PONFERRADAContin an las obras Inauguraci n PONS FERR ART El puente en el Arte Santalla StrartS y QuinSan han creado la Asociaci n de Museos Virtuales cuyo fin es que todos los pueblos independientemente de su poblaci n puedan disponer de un museo de arte El lema es NING N PUEBLO SIN MUSEO Los tres primeros museos ya se han inaugurado en Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata y Madrid El pr ximo ser en Ponferrada y despu s en Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada MUSEUM PROJECT ON CASTLE IN PONFERRADAThe works continue Inauguration PONS FERR ART The bridge in Art Santalla StrartS and QuinSan have created the Association of Virtual Museums whose purpose is that all peoples regardless of their population can have an art museum The motto is NO PEOPLE WITHOUT MUSEUM The first three museums have already opened in Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata and Madrid The next one will be in Ponferrada and then in Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada reinasofiamuseum museodelprado caixaforum museothyssen hermitagemuseum whitneymuseum centrepompidou nationalgallery moma museedorsay louvre met salvadordalimuseum britishmuseum tatemodern guggenheim nycart brooklynmuseum lacmamuseum gemaldegalerie artinstitutechicago ufizzi louvreabudhabi galleriaborghese gettymuseum yaleartgallery sfmoma nationalgalleryofart altepinakothek rijksmuseum

text: El Centre Pompidou M laga es una sede del Centro Nacional de Arte y Cultura Georges Pompidou de Francia ubicada en el espacio denominado El Cubo en la ciudad espa ola de M laga Se trata de la segunda sede externa al centro original parisino y la primera situada fuera de Francia El Cubo consta de dos plantas con metros cuadrados situado en la confluencia de los Paseos de La Farola y de Los Curas Su planta superior es di fana y est coronada por una enorme claraboya con forma de cubo realizada en acero y cristal que hace las veces de lucernario visible y que da nombre al espacio Entre las piezas se encuentran pinturas esculturas instalaciones pel culas y v deos entre las que destacan obras de Frida Khalo Picasso Francis Bacon Giorgio de Chirico Mir o Antoni T pies centrepompidoumalaga Espa a M laga Pompidou Andaluc a Europe Travel Trip Europa Spain instatrip Friends instatravel pictureoftheday picoftheday thebestoftheday bestoftheday instagood instalike instamoment instasize instadaily miradafotografica hallazgosemanal primerolacomunidad landscape vscocam vsco centrepompidou sky ok mencionados

text: Robbery alert of an artwork made by banksy The robbery took place in the night from Sunday to Monday at le Centre Pompidou The work depicts a rat with a masked muzzle waving a pencil This stencil is accompanied by the legend Fifty years since the uprising in Paris The birthplace of modern stencil art The institution said it had filed a complaint today Tuesday September for theft and degradation within a space within its scope It is assumed that the metal panel was cut with a saw We do not own the work that s why we complain about degradation le Centre PompidouThe Pompidou Center recalls that shortly after its completion it decided to protect this stencil by affixing a plate of Plexiglas A first attempt at degradation or theft was halted in July by the security agents of the Pompidou Center doing their rounds around the building says the cultural center streetarteverywhere instagraffiti sprayart art artshow streetart graffiti instastreetart instaart stencil urban stencilart nicestreetart urbanart graffitiart urbanartreleases artrobbery banksystolen stolenartparis helpbanksy centrepompidou

text: I want that That what That But what That To be there to be the strongest to be here getting through wholly warding off nothing devouring all above all eating before going back to the absolute void Antonin ArtaudThe first time I saw original documents by Antonin Artaud was at the Bibliotheque Kandinsky where I used to go for my doctoral research The Kandinsky Library is located at the centrepompidou in Paris France It also serves as the Documentation and Research Centre of the French National Museum of Modern Art Mus e national d art moderne Centre de cr ation industrielle The rule was that one could only enter with a pencil to consult the books so as not to risk ruining or indelibly dirtying those precious printed matters I wouldn t have imagined then that one day I d come in with Avarie books instead which after all are the fruit of the same gesture of care and attention Very proud and honored then to announce that Antoine d Agata s Position s Katrien de Blauwer s I do not want to disappear silently into the night Ion Grigorescu s From static oblivion and Peter Downsbrough s Hence Here Or have all been acquired by the Kandinsky Library They are kept in the R serve the department of rare books I like to imagine that in the future in order to have access to our publications people will not need passwords but wood pencils leAvariesiamonoi fairytaleneverends waysofbeingproud independentpublishing artbooks artistsbooks antoinedagata katriendeblauwer iongrigorescu peterdownsbrough pencils centrepompidou bibliothequekandinsky artlibrary paris antoninartaud books http bibliothequekandinsky centrepompidou fr medias medias aspx INSTANCE INCIPIO

text: Deep respect for Alicia Knock who organized this long overdue retrospective of Ernest Mancoba at Centre Pompidou We see the full depth and breadth of his practice from the early experiments with color and geometry after he moved from South Africa to France and the visually vibrant abstract works from his Cobra period in Denmark to the essence of movement both physical and spiritual in the later paintings and drawings Here is an artist who should be recognized for the amazing art that he brought into this world in a time when being a black South African artist living in Europe led to being excluded from exhibitions and art history The title I shall dance in a different society taken from a quote by Mancoba seems both far away and possible today Please see this show centrepompidou ernestmancoba mancoba stereo aliciaknock exhibition centrepompidou paris painting drawing modern modernism thcentury twentiethcentury abstractart abstraction cobra

text: Today I found out that this work by famous street artist banksy had disappeared The rat an anagram for Art is a recurring character in Banksy s stencil paintings This one was wearing a mask and was armed with a cutter It had appeared on a metal sign just behind the Centre Pompidou on th June Banksy mentioned on his Instagram account that this was a reference to the th anniversary of the student uprisings in Paris It seems that the work was cut out with a saw and stolen presumably to be resold What a shame to have not left it for the people to enjoy That is after all what street art is all about J ai appris aujourd hui la disparition de cette uvre de banksy le plus c l bre des street artists Le rat anagramme du mot Art est l un des personnages r currents dans ses uvres au pochoir Celui ci tait masqu et arm d un cutter Il tait apparu le juin sur un panneau m tallique juste derri re le Centre Pompidou Banksy en avait parl sur son compte Instagram comme un hommage au cinquantenaire des r voltes tudiantes de mai L uvre a vraisemblablement t d mont e la scie et vol e sans doute pour la revendre Quel dommage de ne pas avoir laiss l uvre aux Parisiens C est pourtant l essence du street art streetartparis streetart banksy banksyparis art arthistory histoiredelart centrepompidou pompidou rat banksyrat mai pochoir stencilart museum musee parisart parisculture arturbain arturbainparis parisart parislove parisjetaime parisexpat

name: 2019-09-06 19.12.30 2126887333786451798_centrepompidou.jpg
text: Wanted Banksy artworks stolen in Paris It s certainly never really quiet around this artist It is already the third time that artwork by Banksy is stolen in Paris since his visit in June The latest theft the stencilled piece of a rat wearing a face mask and holding a Stanley knife was opposite the Pompidou Centre until it was cut out of its place on the back of a lit street sign this past Sunday morning at am The piece had a caption Fifty years since the uprising in Paris The birthplace of modern stencil art thereby referring to the May student uprisings but at the same time also crediting illegal stencilled artwork in the street as practised by the likes of Blek le Rat and of course his truly According to Agence France Presse the Pompidou Centre filed a complaint for Theft and damage in their neighbourhood The Pompidou centre also declared We do not own the artwork which is why we don t report it stolen from us but that our neighbourhood was damaged by the theft It is the first time in France that a complaint for theft of a piece of street art is officially lodged Perhaps this is the first step towards a more open reception of the street art movement in the grande nation and while Banksy pieces do tend to get preferential treatment they have also proved to pave the way for change in the past We are most keen to follow the investigation and hear what the verdict is It certainly raises that age old question of who owns artwork in the public space or the rights thereto and do the public have any say in it Here is an article by the BBC and another one in French by AFP https www bbc co uk news world europe https www afp com fr infos un pochoir de banksy vole aux abords du centre pompidou doc jz l

text: The Centre Pompidou is the ugliest building in Paris That was the biting remark made by detractors of the architectural marvel the first major building in Paris to have its infrastructure on the outside On the inside the museum houses over works of modern art from artists like Matisse Picasso and Kandinsky This piece is an installation by Yaacov Agam that was commissioned by President Georges Pompidou himself With every step the viewer takes the shapes in the piece change the colors overlap and you have endless abstract perspectives modernart centrepompidou lifesjourneytravel savorlifesjourney travelplanning luxurytravelplanner paris visitparis

text: En ce moment au Centre Georges Pompidou est expos une artiste dont j aime norm ment le travail Je ne la connaissais pas auparavant et je dois dire que son uvre est pleine de po sie et de douceur Notamment les premi res qui sont teint es d une vidente fusion entre elle et la nature Une vidence qui se constate tout le long de sa vie car bien qu elle ait multipli e les supports de cr ation elle n a pas ou peu vari e sa technique et ses compositions Ses premi res uvres tonnamment comparable ses derni res et mes yeux c est ce qui fait la force de cette artiste Elle est d ailleurs expos e en m me temps que son mari Ernest Celle dont je vous parle ce soir c est la sculptrice Sonja Ferlov Mancoba Et c est l une des premi res uvres pr sentes dans l exposition et l une de ses premi res uvres tout court Levende grene Branches vivantes qui m a donn envie d crire et pourtant durant des semaines je n ai pas r ussi crire une seule ligne depuis le d but de l exposition soit le juin Finalement j avais un peu mis de c t cette id e jusqu au moment o je me suis retrouv post une nouvelle fois dans cette exposition Toujours anim de cette envie de dire quelque chose propos de cette artiste je me suis naturellement pos devant la sculpture To levende vaesener deux tres vivants de et c est l j ai eu le d clic Tellement que les premi res phrases de mon texte sont le titre de cette uvre L image qui illustre donc ce texte est la seconde sculpture To levende vaesener deux tres vivants et je vous ai quand m me mis Levende grene Branches vivantes apr s le texte Je ne peux que vous inviter d couvrir son travail ainsi que celui de son mari Bonne soir e vous poesie poetry texte photo fr d ricmur french inspiration po sie photography sonjaferlovmancoba centrepompidou modernart sculpture exposition museum paris frenchpoetry

text: PROYECTO DE MUSEO SOBRE CASTILLO EN PONFERRADAContin an las obras Inauguraci n Capic a del a o PONS FERR ART El puente en el Arte Santalla StrartS y QuinSan han creado la Asociaci n de Museos Virtuales cuyo fin es que todos los pueblos independientemente de su poblaci n puedan disponer de un museo de arte El lema es NING N PUEBLO SIN MUSEO Los tres primeros museos ya se han inaugurado en Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata y Madrid El pr ximo ser en Ponferrada y despu s en Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada MUSEUM PROJECT ON CASTLE IN PONFERRADAThe works continue Inauguration Capic a of the year PONS FERR ART The bridge in Art Santalla StrartS and QuinSan have created the Association of Virtual Museums whose purpose is that all peoples regardless of their population can have an art museum The motto is NO PEOPLE WITHOUT MUSEUM The first three museums have already opened in Lapuebla de Labarca San Juan de la Mata and Madrid The next one will be in Ponferrada and then in Vitoria Alovera Arganza Azuqueca Sancti Petri Trillo Laguardia Guadalajara Elciego Yebra Logro o La Puebla de Ponferrada reinasofiamuseum museodelprado caixaforum museothyssen hermitagemuseum whitneymuseum centrepompidou nationalgallery moma museedorsay louvre met salvadordalimuseum britishmuseum tatemodern guggenheim nycart brooklynmuseum lacmamuseum gemaldegalerie artinstitutechicago ufizzi louvreabudhabi galleriaborghese gettymuseum yaleartgallery sfmoma nationalgalleryofart altepinakothek rijksmuseum

name: 2019-09-09 04.32.05 2128618543154387500_centrepompidou.jpg
text: Ok so not the best photo taken by our sweet waiter my friend and I are in the dark while Lily has an eerie glow from the candlelight lol BUT it was such an unforgettable evening that I had to share This is one of the things I love about traveling We have made so many wonderful friends over the years We just met Linda and her lovely family a few weeks ago while in Sardinia We randomly pulled up to the same jam and cheese place literally a country home in the middle of nowhere After trying and buying some delicious products we exchanged info and I told Linda I would reach out to her in Paris THEN they walked past the table we were seated at outside a restaurant This was two days later in a totally different town in Sardinia We recognized each other and we invited them to join us for what turned into a four hour dinner We talked and laughed over several bottles of wine and left as great friends So by the time Lily and I arrived in Paris days later seeing Linda felt like meeting an old friend She and her family are planning to visit us in Los Angeles soon I am so grateful to her for making our last night in Paris so special whatiloveabouttravel internationalfriends paris eiffeltower centrepompidou eatdrinktravelmom eatdrinktravel motherdaughter motherhood momblogger mommyblogger mommyandme momlife momsofinstagram toddlerlife thisisfour travelgram travel travelphotographer travelblogger familytravel lilyelizabeth internationallily kidsofinstagram kidstagram familieswhotravel adventureswithlily buildingmemories onenightinparis

text: Philosophy of Art Deleuze s Francis Bacon Instructor Evrim Emir SayersWhen two iconoclasts of the th century one an artist the other a philosopher meet there happens Gilles Deleuze s Francis Bacon The Logic of Sensation When Francis Bacon creator of some of the most disturbing imagery in th century art declares that I believe in deeply ordered chaos it is not surprising that he is heard by Gilles Deleuze who sees not only art but also philosophy as a means of confronting chaos To Deleuze it would be a mistake to think that the painter works on a white and virgin surface The entire surface is already invested virtually with all kinds of clich s which the painter will have to break with What are these clich s And how does Bacon break with them without descending into chaos In this course we will trace these questions through a rigorous reading of Deleuze s Francis Bacon Deleuze is not an art critic He engages Bacon not through an aesthetic appraisal but by creating a series of philosophical concepts that enable a whole new way of thinking Western painting through Bacon Armed with these concepts we will reimagine the history of painting from nineteenth century figurative art to avant garde movements such as impressionism abstract painting abstract expressionism and finally Deleuze s figural as exemplified by Bacon Throughout the course we will not only familiarize ourselves with modern painting but will also develop new methods of thinking via painting Maximum enrollment SCHEDULESundays pmOctober November hours weeks expobacon francisbacon deleuze centrepompidou modernart philosophy philosophyofart gillesdeleuze painting philosopher artlovers painter philosophyofart aesthetics arthistory expatparis parisexpat studyabroad expatsinparis beaubourg art artist parismaville parisian parisienne parisjetaime parismonamour criticalthinking parisfrance reading bookworm

text: Fantastic piece of Stefan Bruggemann at the Centre Pompidou Titled Headlines and Last Lines in the Movies Guernica this work is part of a series of works started by the artist in The term Headlines refers to headlines that appear in the headlines this is where Br ggemann draws his headlines textual sources during the week in which he does his work While Last Lines are quotes taken from movie ends from Citizen Kane to Wolf Wall Street By mixing these two types of sentences or titles the artist proposes a world saturated with information where information mixes with fiction Our faces and identities are reflected and constructed through this distorted mirror of the world For the rd edition of the festival Extra and echoing with the opening of the exhibition Bacon in all letters an invitation was launched to Stefan Br ggemann His proposal for the festival Extra is an amazing proposition for intervention in the Forum suspending a gigantic painting on the shimmering surface and covered with writings Visible double sided from the top of the Forum to the bottom this piece plays with the space in a spectacular way This mirror image is accompanied by a soundtrackText Pieces read by Iggy Pop in which Iggy Pop recites with his unique voice fragments of Stefan Bruggemann texts Impossible to miss curated by Jean Max Colard tstefanbruggemann jeanmaxcolard centrepompidou festivalextra hauserandwirth eugeniolopez centrepompidou stefanbruggemann hauserwirth parraromero

text: Beyond Picasso A visceral passion for painting and photography His name is inextricably linked to Picasso of whom he was a muse and lover but in reality it was much more Model poet painter and photographer Dora Maar was one of the pioneers of women s artistic emancipation in the golden years of Parisian surrealism To the century Henriette Theodora Markovi Dora Maar was born in Paris in to a Croatian father and a French mother He spent his adolescence between Paris and Buenos Aires where his father an architect had received important assignments As a child she was fascinated by de Chirico s works and by the new architectural currents and in the s she studied at the cole et Ateliers d Arts D coratifs in Paris then attended the Acad mie Lhote where she met Henri Cartier Bresson and finally passionate about photography and enrolled at the cole de Photographie de la Ville de Paris Read Dora Maar beyond Picasso full article on handbookcostasmeralda com clicking this link https www handbookcostasmeralda com dora maar oltre picasso handbookcostasmeralda handbookcostasmeralda centrepompidou centrepompidou doramaar doramaar

text: Jeff Koons La r trospective centrepompidou Balloon Dog Personnification m me de cette id e profond ment am ricaine qui est celle de la r ussite Paris organis la premi re r trospective europ enne consacr e Jeff Koons du novembre au avril Tel un Andy Warhol des temps modernes m me si il refuse de s apparenter lui Koons n a de cesse de s interroger sur le monde dans lequel il vit et se questionne sur les objets de cultes pour mieux s amuser des codes Il utilise de mani re astucieuse les m dias pour jouer du personnage qu il s est construit Ainsi comme ses pr d cesseur issus du Pop Art il use des motifs et des arch types de la culture de masse Koons fait parti des artistes les plus embl matiques de notre si cle mais il est galement le plus controvers de la sc ne contemporaine Admiratif de l art du pass que l artiste marque sa volont de renouer avec le classique en int grant des chefs d uvres comme dans sa s rie Il est galement un fin connaisseur de l art de son temps Koons fa onn une uvre singuli re qui lui a permi de bousculer le monde de l art Il n a de cesse de d fier la critique en questionnant de mani re permanente et avec une certaine acuit le concept m me de valeur Koons met plus que jamais en jeu la d finition des fronti res de l art tel que l avait fait Marcel Duchamp avec ses c l bres Ready Made remettant en question le concept pourtant profond ment ancr d une uvre d art Koons exposition paris centrepompidou article photography artist balloondog instagram

text: Coming up next week in Paris The centrepompidou will screen Lothar Baumgarten s seminal film Origin of the Night Amazon Cosmos on September at pm Shot between and the film is based on a Tupi Indian myth about the origin of the night and depicts a landscape passing from night into day back into night According to Baumgarten binary oppositions such as inside and outside day and night the new and ancient world myth and travel nature and culture are present in the film The structure of the images is as multilayered as the levels of a tropical forest and its myths its smells and sounds LotharBaumgarten centrepompidou

text: CONCERT Dominique Gonzalez Foerster Exotourisme centrepompidou Paris September On the occasion of the Festival Extra Exotourism the musical project of the artist Dominique Gonzalez Foerster and the musician and performer Julien Perez will make a concert in the Textodrome the small room of the Pompidou Center and renamed by the artist for Extra With its retro futuristic melodies inspired by both the film Blade Runner and the French cold wave of the s Exotourism invites the viewer to enter the mellow and hushed atmosphere Image Dominique Gonzalez Foerster Exotourisme Elevation Frequencies Gstaad Photo Dominqiue Gonzalez Foerster dominiquegonzalezfoerster centrepompidou paris festivalextra exotourism

text: Centre Pompidou designed as an evolving spatial diagram by architects Renzo Piano and Richard Rogers it contains a lot of characteristics that make it unique in the world For this building an architectural competition was announced the first time in France that the competition was opened to architects from the whole world over it attracted competitors from different countries This was the first major example of an inside out building in architectural history with its structural system mechanical systems and circulation exposed on the exterior of the building The New York Times noted that the design of the Centre turned the architecture world upside down Initially all of the functional structural elements of the building were colour coded green pipes are plumbing blue ducts are for climate control electrical wires are in yellow and circulation elements and devices for safety are red FOLLOW travel with no luggage CentrePompidou pompidou museum modernistarchitecture architecture lovers paris iloveparis parisjetaime parismaville thisisparis ig paris igersparis igersfrance hello france travelholic couplegoals travelideas travelcouple coupletravels travelingcouple instatravel instapic traveladdict parisienne parisianlife parisstyle parisphoto cityscape travelwithnoluggage

text: Je pr pare une longue story pour parler de la sublime expo francisbacon au centrepompidou mais cet artiste me fascine tellement qu il me semble que le format ad quat serait plut t un podcast de heures Je voulais toutefois poster d s aujourd hui cette uvre que j ai d couverte hier au centrepompidou qui introduit la p riode couverte par l exposition Sans rien en savoir elle voque d j toute la violence et la douceur de son sujet On peut d j se raconter beaucoup d histoires se laisser aller bien des sentiments en l observant Mais quand on sait qu il s agit d un triptyque la m moire de son amant GeorgeDyer qui est mort d une overdose l h tel des Saints P res deux jours avant l ouverture de la premi re et tr s importante retrospective de Bacon Paris elle prend une toute autre dimension On y retrouve tellement d obsessions de Bacon les images de lutteurs les portraits de son amant tous deux r interpr t s d apr s des photographies comme pour dire en peinture ce que l appareil ne peut pas fixer Il y a une gicl e blanche sur la troisi me image comme sur tous les tableaux qu il voulait charger d rotisme Cette uvre repr sente tout ce que j aime chez Bacon une puissance qui rend inutile l analyse et le discours Mais aussi une iconographie riche et cryptique qui rend l oeuvre toujours plus fascinante mesure qu on apprend la lire J ai h te de vous parler du reste de l exposition rendez vous demain en story parisexpo expoparis parisart artmoderne expositionparis entouteslettres

text: Aujourd hui on vous fait d couvrir le travail de Sonja Ferlov Mancoba Artiste danoise elle suit une premi re formation en peinture avant de se tourner vers la sculpture En elle s installe Paris et c toie Alberto Giacometti Max Ernst Joan Miro et son futur poux l artiste sud africain Ernest Mancoba la crois e de formes abstraites et figuratives ses sculptures et ses dessins empruntent l art africain et pr colombien jusqu au surr alisme Ses uvres d voilent une fa on de penser l individu comme un tre en perp tuel devenir ExpoSonjaMancoba jusqu au septembre Today we present you the work of Sonja Ferlov Mancoba Danish artist she first learned painting before turning to sculpture In she came in Paris and met Alberto Giacometti Max Ernst Joan Miro and her future husband the South African artist Ernest Mancoba Between abstract and figurative shapes her sculptures and drawings are inspired by African and pre Columbian art and Surrealism Her works reveal a vision of individual as a constantly becoming being Our Sonja Ferlov Mancoba exhibition until September CentrePompidou DerniersJours LastDays SonjaFerlovMancoba ModernArt Sonja Ferlov Mancoba Le combattant Pl tre collection particuli re Anders Sune Berg Adagp Paris

text: Aujourd hui on vous fait d couvrir le travail de Sonja Ferlov Mancoba Artiste danoise elle suit une premi re formation en peinture avant de se tourner vers la sculpture En elle s installe Paris et c toie Alberto Giacometti Max Ernst Joan Miro et son futur poux l artiste sud africain Ernest Mancoba la crois e de formes abstraites et figuratives ses sculptures et ses dessins empruntent l art africain et pr colombien jusqu au surr alisme Ses uvres d voilent une fa on de penser l individu comme un tre en perp tuel devenir ExpoSonjaMancoba jusqu au septembre Today we present you the work of Sonja Ferlov Mancoba Danish artist she first learned painting before turning to sculpture In she came in Paris and met Alberto Giacometti Max Ernst Joan Miro and her future husband the South African artist Ernest Mancoba Between abstract and figurative shapes her sculptures and drawings are inspired by African and pre Columbian art and Surrealism Her works reveal a vision of individual as a constantly becoming being Our Sonja Ferlov Mancoba exhibition until September CentrePompidou DerniersJours LastDays SonjaFerlovMancoba ModernArt Sonja Ferlov Mancoba sculptures Sans titre Terre cuite Silkeborg Museum Jorn Anders Sune Berg Adagp Paris

text: KAZIMIR MALEVICH CROSSED LINESRED CROSS ON BLACK CIRCLE MYSTICAL SUPREMATISM Oil on canvas ABROAD IN Malevich invented Suprematism in His non objective art form These paintings went abroad to Poland and Germany with Malevich to showcase Suprematism He went to the bauhaus DISPUTED DATESee for further detail Perhaps Malevich did created this specially for his In Malevich said painting was outdated and spent time writing and teaching including in red vitebsk now belarus from DELETIONSSee The red line is thinned from the original thicker pencilled outline Note shows pencilled lines for a crossing line form The red cross creates an association with the Roman cross of Christianity Note The Russian Orthodox cross is closer with the additional crossed line GREAT PAINTERSaid Anatoli Lunarcharsky Commissar of the Enlightenment about Malevich in But made a point that Malevich s muddled writings that included Christian mysticism were likely to sow confuse in the German audience Another issue is that the Suprematists did not tend to refer to the cross But instead tended to refer to the crossed lines IN THE FLOWSee highlights the quick execution of his idea Note the paint bleeding and pencil lines IDEA OF A CIRCLESee reveals that the circle is not truly a geometric circle Malevich was not using the compass of Constructivists such as Rodchenko Popova or Stepanova Suprematist painting as a human hand painted form still lives here WHERE CAN I SEE THESE PAINTINGSBoth paintings live in Amsterdam My photos of May from chagalllissitzkymalevitch exhibition in centrepompidou beaubourg paris SUPREMATISM OF THE SPIRIT Oil on panel Circle cross red geometricart abstractart unovis kazimirmalevich malevich russianart suprematism russianavantgarde russia ukrainianartist russianartist constructivism revolution Inspired by a future radioflomm podcast conversation with johnn nelsonn

text: Francis Bacon In Memory of George Dyer Bacon au Centre Pompidou l exposition somptueuse d un peintre de g nie Hormis cinq ou six oeuvres l exposition commence lorsque l amant de Francis Bacon George Dyer se suicide Paris le octobre deux jours avant l inauguration de sa r trospective au Grand Palais Elle recouvre donc les vingt derni res ann es du peintre anglais mort Madrid en l ge de ans De fait apr s une petite salle servant d introduction les trois grands triptyques consacr s l amant disparu occupent la premi re grande salle celui peint juste apr s le suicide la m moire de George Dyer et les deux hommages post rieurs ao t et mai juin Le ton est donn c est une splendeur Le titre de l exposition Bacon en toutes lettres se justifie par le fait que le peintre fut inspir par ses lectures surtout par la po sie et notamment celle de l Am ricain T S Eliot ou la trag die Eschyle Shakespeare etc mais aussi par certains textes de Nietzsche de Georges Bataille ou de son ami Michel Leiris On oublie les rumeurs sur la suppos e violence et la crudit de la peinture de Bacon pour s merveiller de la magnificence des coloris magnificence port e par une extraordinaire science de la composition On sort la fois bloui et conscient du g nie de ce peintre sans aucun doute l un des plus grands artistes du XXe si cle The Estate of Francis Bacon Adagp Huile et letraset sur toile triptyque x cm Beyeler Museum Photo H Maertens Retrouvez sur telerama fr la critique d Olivier C na dans T l rama le portrait de Francis Bacon et dans les kiosque le hors s rie de T l rama indispensable avec un texte sur la peinture de Francis Bacon de Jonathan Littell un entretien mythique du peintre avec Marguerite Duras une biographie de Bacon par lui m me Bacon sous l objectif d Irving Penn Bill Brandt Cecil Beaton John Deakin Marc Trivier ou Peter Beard En kiosques voir Bacon en toutes lettres jusqu au janvier Centre Pompidou FrancisBacon ExpoBacon centrepompidou text: CentrePompidou continues its re examination of key th century works by devoting a major exhibition to Francis Bacon The last major French exhibition of this artist s work was held in at the Centre Pompidou More than twenty years later the exhibiton titled Francis Bacon Books and Painting presents paintings dating from the year of the retrospective event at the national galleries of the Grand Palais to his final works in Didier Ottinger is the curator of this innovative exploration of the influence of literature in Francis Bacon s painting Francis Bacon Female nude standing in doorway FrancisBacon CentrePompidou Exhibition Retrospective

text: Such soothing dreamlike happy uplifting peaceful new body of work by BernardFrize Journey in Autumn galerieperrotin New York BernardFrize s solo exhibition displays a new body of work by the artist Critic and artist Jessica Stockholder describes the sensitive experience created by Bernard Frize s paintings The layers of content that a Frize painting generates arise as one becomes aware of how the painting is made what it is made out of how it acts on our biological perceptual apparatus how our reception of the work is responsive to the light and scale of the circumstance we find the painting in and the various points of reference outside of it that a viewer is able to coalesce in mind And then this edifice built in mind rattles together with the ongoing sensual experience of standing in front of the painting Bernard Frize Journey in Autumn Perrotin New York Until October Bernard Frize just closed a formidable yr retrospective centrepompidou in Paris entitled Sans Repentir Without Remorse AbstractArt PerrotinNewYork Perrotin emmanuelperrotin LeCentrePompidou paris centrepompidou abstraction abstractpainting abstract frenchart art arte kunst konst nayoung seungyeon artselfie artlife artlover artlovers artcollector artcollectors artcurator artadvisory artsdvisor destineeross desti knee joakimvonditmar

text: Bacon en toutes lettres centrepompidou until january curated by Didier Ottinger I remember him teaching contemporary art at Ecole du Louvre in the nineties Here one can see the work of Bacon and also hear litterary references Conrad Nietszche Bataille etc read by actors The best Bacon exhibition I have seen was Bacon and the tradition of art fondationbeyeler in Before it has been shown in Vienna It emphasized the influence Bacon had from paintings from Velasquez to Picasso Today in an interview he also spoked about movie director Eisenstein In Beyeler himself was alive I remembered him making his late afternoon daily walk towards the fondation It was relatively fast for a man of his age He gave me the impression of someone who did not want to lose time fondationbacon monaco ireland england france southafrica francisbacon paintings modernart centrepompidou fondationbeyeler eisenstein pablopicasso velasquez parislavielafete

text: Prehistory With politics spinning out of control with the modern as terrifying as it was exhilarating many artists in the nineteenth and especially twentieth centuries found a counterpoint to the phrenetic murderous machine age to all the supreme crazy in the art made before art began Momentous discoveries in the caves of Lascaux and Altamira geological investigations penetrating the layers of the Earth and museum displays of objects made by Palaeolithic and Neolithic man caused artists as various as Caspar David Friedrich paulcezanne PaulKlee Max Ernst and JosephBeuys whose works I photographed among many many others to ponder the impenetrability of time as set against what could be discovered about early man to consider essential human characteristics and their visual expression ranging from the fashioning of the essential feminine those many so called Venuses all bust belly and booty to the desire to paint pictures in the first place or to carve painstakingly almost painfully beautiful ritual objects and adornments Our relationships with animals These works those artefacts as ancient as art itself and the timeless glories of the last hundred years and a little more were gathered together in an exhibition Pr histoire une nigme moderne that s closing tomorrow at the CentrePompidou a show both meditated and thrilling It was like rafting through dark caverns with torches and occasional shafts of light to show us the way Led by these works we re offered the chance to escape the tedious complexities of today while helping us to get them in proportion greatcuration mariastavrinaki if this is she cecile debrayamar r milabrusse inspiring

text: flommist malevichsquared KAZIMIR MALEVICH CROSSED LINESRED CROSS ON BLACK CIRCLE MYSTICAL SUPREMATISM Oil on canvas ABROAD IN Malevich invented Suprematism in His non objective art form These paintings went abroad to Poland and Germany with Malevich to showcase Suprematism He went to the bauhaus DISPUTED DATESee for further detail Perhaps Malevich did created this specially for his In Malevich said painting was outdated and spent time writing and teaching including in red vitebsk now belarus from DELETIONSSee The red line is thinned from the original thicker pencilled outline Note shows pencilled lines for a crossing line form The red cross creates an association with the Roman cross of Christianity Note The Russian Orthodox cross is closer with the additional crossed line GREAT PAINTERSaid Anatoli Lunarcharsky Commissar of the Enlightenment about Malevich in But made a point that Malevich s muddled writings that included Christian mysticism were likely to sow confuse in the German audience Another issue is that the Suprematists did not tend to refer to the cross But instead tended to refer to the crossed lines IN THE FLOWSee highlights the quick execution of his idea Note the paint bleeding and pencil lines IDEA OF A CIRCLESee reveals that the circle is not truly a geometric circle Malevich was not using the compass of Constructivists such as Rodchenko Popova or Stepanova Suprematist painting as a human hand painted form still lives here WHERE CAN I SEE THESE PAINTINGSBoth paintings live in Amsterdam My photos of May from chagalllissitzkymalevitch exhibition in centrepompidou beaubourg paris SUPREMATISM OF THE SPIRIT Oil on panel Circle cross red geometricart abstractart unovis kazimirmalevich malevich russianart suprematism russianavantgarde ukrainianartist russianartist constructivism revolutionInspired by conversation with johnn nelsonn

text: BERNARD FRIZE JOURNEY IN AUTUMN Happy colorful Sunday on our way to Autumn Now at galerieperrotin Until Oct Entering the autumn in NYC with colors of leaves the sky and bernardfrize colorful brushes rebelling any grid The layers of content that a Frize painting generates arise as one becomes aware of how the painting is made what it is made out of how it acts on our biological perceptual apparatus how our reception of the work is responsive to the light and scale of the circumstance we find the painting in and the various points of reference outside of it that a viewer is able to coalesce in mind And then this edifice built in mind rattles together with the ongoing sensual experience of standing in front of the painting This awkwardness inherent to the relationship between paintings and language is only part of the story my experience of Frize s language is consistent with my experience of the paintings themselves Each painting presents a coherent often object like very factual index of eventfulness Loved and totally agree with this lyrical but insightful description of his work by Jessica Stockholder also reported in the catalog and press release This show follows the solo exhibitions at Perrotin tokyo and paris as well as a major presentation of the artist s work at the centrepompidou in Paris bernardfrize bernardfrizeartist contemporaryart artecontemporanea artadvisory artgram perrotingallery perrotin perrotinnewyork artgallery nycartgallery artlovers painting colors autumn sunday newyork nyc newyorkcity

text: A huge exhibition has opened at the centrepompidou featuring sixty paintings including of Bacon s triptychs We hope to see the show before it closes First image Self Portrait by Francis BaconSecond image is a portrait of Francis Bacon taken in London On show here at the collective The picture is a little blurred the photographer a little drunk Bacon ordered many bottles of Champagne and was very generous with his bottles It was hard to keep up with him for many reasons one of them was he was extraordinarily flamboyant with his hand gestures and as a result generally threw most of his drinks into the air which meant that his companions drank three glasses for every one he consumed Alastair Thain

text: EXPLOSANTE FIXE PHOTOGRAPHIE SURR ALISME par Rosalind KRAUSS Jane LIVINGSTON Dawn ADES Editions Centre Georges Pompidou Hazan Paris Fort petit in couverture toil e rouge sous jaquette photo pages Texte en fran ais illustr de reproductions photographiques noir blanc in texte et hors texte Ouvrage r alis dans le cadre de l exposition ponyme au Mus e national d art moderne Centre Georges Pompidou Paris du Avril au Juin Explosante fixe photographie et surr alisme montre comment quelques pionniers mirent au service de la subjectivit surr aliste la facult de constat de cet il qu est l objectif photographique Ce livre r cuse aussi l id e re ue qui veut qu une photographie surr aliste soit n cessairement une image truqu e Les surr alistes ont au contraire largement exploit la photographie v rit pour illustrer leurs textes litt raires ou th oriques Personne auparavant Walter Benjamin except n avait tudi ces photographies dans le contexte du roman de la po sie ou de la prose qu elles accompagnaient lors de leur premi re publication Ce livre abonde en images fantastiques n es de la manipulation en chambre noire des jeux de la lumi re et du hasard Erotiques inqui tantes d concertantes ou humoristiques elles sont parmi les plus belles et les plus envoutantes que la vision surr aliste ait inspir es des artistes tels que Man Ray Marcel Duchamp Ren Magritte Max Ernst Andr Breton Brassa Salvador Dali Andr Kert sz Raoul Ubac Jacques Andr Boiffard Lee Miller et Hans Bellmer ExplosanteFixe PhotographieEtSurrealisme PhotographyAndSurrealism exposition exhibition CentreGeorgesPompidou CentrePompidou livrephoto photobook photographie surrealisme photography surrealism noiretblanc blackandwhite balckandwhitephotography PhotoParMauriceTabard PhotoByMauriceTabard MauriceTabard
